Ing '''tukal''' o '''luke''' (''Nelumbo nucifera''), a ausan dang '''Indian lotus''', '''sacred lotus''', '''bean of India''', o kabud namu '''lotus''' king Ingles, metung ya kareng adwang species a mabibye king danum king familia [[Family (Biology)|family]] [[Nelumbo]]naceae. Ing lagyung Linnaean binomial a ''Nelumbo nucifera'' ([[Joseph Gaertner|Gaertn.]]) ing kasalungsungang kikilalanan a lagyu para kaniting species, a makabili king lalam ning sadya o dating lagyung ''Nelumbium speciosum'' ([[Carl Ludwig Willdenow|Willd.]]) ampong ''[[Nymphaea]] nelumbo'', bukud pa kareng aliwa. Iti metung yang tanaman a pilmihan (''perennial'') a mabibye king danum o aquatico. Nung masanting ing pamikatagun, dakal lang banwang malyaring tumubu deng kayang bini, at ing pekamalambat o pamanubu, ibat kareng butul o bining maki idad a 1,300&nbsp;banwang mekwa king lalam ning malanging dayatan recovered from a (''dry lakebed'') king [[pangulu]] [[aslagan]]g [[China]].<ref>{{cite journal | doi = 10.3732/ajb.89.2.236 | url = http://www.amjbot.org/content/89/2/236.abstract | title = Long-living lotus: Germination and soil  -irradiation of centuries-old fruits, and cultivation, growth, and phenotypic abnormalities of offspring | year = 2002 | last1 = Shen-Miller | first1 = J. | last2 = Schopf | first2 = J. W. | last3 = Harbottle | first3 = G. | last4 = Cao | first4 = R.-j. | last5 = Ouyang | first5 = S. | last6 = Zhou | first6 = K.-s. | last7 = Southon | first7 = J. R. | last8 = Liu | first8 = G.-h. | journal = American Journal of Botany | volume = 89 | issue = 2 | pages = 236â€“47 | pmid = 21669732}}</ref>

Katutubu ya king malisangan o tropical nang dake ning [[Asia]] ampo king [[Queensland]], [[Australia]],<ref>Perry, F. <u>Flowers of the World</u> Bonanza Books, 1972. p. 192-193</ref><ref>Serventy, V; Raymond, R. <u>Lakes & Rivers of Australia</u> Summit Books, 1980. p. 102-103</ref> it is commonly cultivated in [[water garden]]s. It is also the [[National emblem|national flower]] of [[India]] and [[Vietnam]].

